      <h2 class="subsubheader">Our Mission</h2><br>
      <p>When people are to know half-baked knowledge, it is easy for misunderstandings to take hold. This is why this organization aims to clear up falsified information as well as the FIlipino name. dysPHoria hopes to open the eyes of the FIlipinos to the discrimination its countrymen are experiencing, and to learn to fight back against normalizing these discriminatory acts. Lastly, it set its sights on connecting the history of the Philippines to the current discrimination that its country is experiencing in hopes to find a solution to these discriminatory acts.</p><br>
      <p>Due to the discrimination against Filipinos that is still prevalent everywhere, Filipinos might feel dissatisfied or unhappy that they are Filipinos. The dissatisfaction that a FIlipino may feel towards their race is an important topic to address as it may result in further inferiority complex. This might then result in a person’s acceptance of the violation of their rights. Thus, the dysphoria that a Filipino might feel from these past situations need to be addressed so that Filipinos would know what their rights are, and the reason behind these discriminatory acts.</p><br>

      <br><hr class="line-light"><br>

      <h2 class="subsubheader">Our Vision</h2><br>
