      <h2 class="subsubheader">Introduction: Racial Discrimination in the Past and Present</h2><br>
      <p>Since the time of the Spanish conquest, Filipinos have faced various forms of discrimination from foreigners and from fellow Filipinos. To this day, there are still lasting effects from the Philippine occupation - such as Filipinos judging their fellow Filipinos and treating their own race as inferior to other races.</p><br>
      <p>In the cases of discrimination against Filipinos from foreigners, there are many cases of discrimination against Filipinos working abroad. This happens because foreigners think that Filipinos have a lower status than other races. It can be seen here that not only historically, discrimination against Filipinos by foreigners is widespread but also today.</p><br>
      <p>Apart from foreigners, there is also discrimination against fellow Filipinos. There are companies in the Philippines that even fellow Filipinos experience discrimination. The skin whitening industry is also widespread in the Philippines. Most skin products often have bleaching ingredients. Women in the Philippines insist on following the standard of beauty where whites excel while blacks are looked down upon. Some Filipinos view differently based on the color of their skin; white Filipinos are more “attractive” and “rich” while brown Filipinos are “dirty”. The popularity of bleach products is rooted in the ingrained racism that dates back to the time of the Spaniards.</p><br>
      <p>Colonial ideologies are now being brought into the present where they are influencing the minds of Filipinos today. Therefore, discrimination against Filipinos can be consnidered to be rampant from then until now.</p><br>

      <br><hr class="line-light"><br>

      <h2 class="subsubheader">Why is Racial Discrimination in the Philippines an important topic?</h2><br>
      <p>Discrimination has a deep connection with the history of the Philippines. Even though we can consider the Philippines as free from its colonizers, the events during the colonization of the Philippines still have a big impact on the present. This is because discrimination against Filipinos still exists within the country and outside of it.</p><br>
